Description: Wall fragment of large open vase. Coarse yellow-buff clay. Dipinto inscription.
Curator's comments: M. Pesenti suggests that the piece may be Cypro-Levantine. The dipinto remains are unhelpful, though they would seem to in a much later cursive style.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 659)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.375)
